Key Match Events: The Rangers won 3-1 in the completion of the suspended game, then took the nightcap 4-3.
Travis Jankowski made a catch high above the wall to take a walk-off homer away from Andrew Vaughn in the ninth inning of the second game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played with a sparse crowd.
Others: The White Sox lost their 102nd and 103rd games in the two games.
